OL,3,CTrains cancelled and schools close as
OL,4,Crecord-breaking heat predicted
OL,6,FTrains have been cancelled and
OL,7,Fhundreds of schools have shut their
OL,8,Fdoors as record-breaking temperatures
OL,9,Fin Wales are predicted for a second
OL,10,Fday.
OL,12,FLarge parts of south Wales are covered
OL,13,Fby a rare red heat weather warning
OL,14,Funtil midnight on Thursday.
OL,16,FThe record for the UK's hottest June
OL,17,Fday was broken for the fourth time on
OL,18,FWednesday, with a provisional
OL,19,Ftemperature of 36.1C breaking the
OL,20,Fprevious record from the summer of
OL,21,F1976.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G1/5
